sentences: The family lived in Cupertino from about the time Hua was nine to 18, though his father moved to Taiwan to pursue work and Hua often spent summers and other school vacations there.
He next attended Harvard University to study Asian-American literature in graduate school, earning a PhD in the History of American Civilization department (American Studies) in 2008.
His 2012 essay for Lucky Peach about suburban Chinatowns was nominated for a 2012 James Beard Award for food writing.

His book, A Floating Chinaman: Fantasy and Failure Across the Pacific, was published in June 2016 by Harvard University Press.
He was a 2016 National Fellow for the New America Foundation.
In 2017, Hsu became a staff writer at The New Yorker.
